The '''''Flora of North America North of Mexico''''' (usually referred to as '''''FNA''''') is a multivolume work describing the [[native plant]]s of [[North America]]. Much of the Flora is already available online.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.efloras.org/flora_page.aspx?flora_id=1 |title=Flora of North America |work=eFloras.org |date= |accessdate=2012-11-05}}</ref> It is expected to fill 30 volumes when completed and will be the first work to treat all of the known flora north of [[Mexico]].

It is a collaboration of over 800 authors, who collaborate over the web.<ref>{{citation | doi = 10.1109/HICSS.1998.651712 | title = Managing cognitive overload in the Flora of North America project | year = 1998 | author = Tomlinson, K.L. | volume = 2 | page = 296 | last2 = Sanchez | first2 = J.A. | last3 = Spasser | first3 = M.A. | last4 = Schnase | first4 = J.L. }}</ref>

