===Death of Kagutsuchi===
After the agony, Izanami dies. At the time Izanagi crept moaning about the body and mourned her death. From his tears {{nihongo|'''[[Nakisawame]]'''|[[:ja:ナキサワメ|泣沢女神]]}} was born. Subsequently Izanagi buried Izanami on [[Mount Hiba (Shimane)|Mount Hiba]]. His sadness turned into anger and he decided to kill Kagutsuchi with a ten-grasp<ref group="nb" name="grasp"/> sword called {{nihongo|'''[[Ame-no-ohabari]]'''|[[:ja:天之尾羽張]]|extra=also known as Itsu-no-ohabari}}.<ref name="kojiki-p79">{{Harvnb|Chamberlain|2008|p=79}}</ref><ref name="kojiki-p80-81">{{Harvnb|Chamberlain|2008|pp=80–81}}</ref>

From the blood of Kagutsuchi the following gods emerged:<ref name="kojiki-p80-81"/>

# {{nihongo|'''[[Iwasaku]]'''|[[:ja:イワサク・ネサク|石折神]]}}<ref group="nb">Chamberlain: Ihasaku</ref>
# {{nihongo|'''[[Nesaku]]'''|[[:ja:イワサク・ネサク|根折神]]}}
# {{nihongo|'''{{Interlanguage link multi|Iwatsutsunoo|2=en|3=Iwatsutsunoo|preserve=1}}'''|[[:ja:イワツツノオ|石筒之男神]]}}
#: The gods above were born from the blood that fell from the tip of the sword in the rocks.
# {{nihongo|'''[[Mikahayahi]]'''|甕速日神}}
# {{nihongo|'''[[Hihayahi]]'''|樋速日神}}
# {{nihongo|'''[[Takemikazuchi|Takemikagutsuchinoo]]'''|建御雷之男神}}, also known as {{nihongo|'''Takefutsu'''|建布都神}} or {{nihongo|'''Toyofutsu'''|豊布都神}}
#: The gods above were born from the blood that fell from the blade of the sword.
# {{nihongo|'''[[Kuraokami]]'''|[[:ja:淤加美神|闇淤加美神]]}}
# {{nihongo|'''[[Kuramitsuha]]'''|[[:ja:クラミツハ|闇御津羽神]]}}
#: The gods above were born from the blood that fell from the handle of the sword.

Also, from the body of Kagutsuchi the following gods were born:<ref name="kojiki-p80-81"/>
# {{nihongo|'''[[Masakayamatsumi]]'''|正鹿山津見神}}, emerged from Kagutsuchi's head;
